texts.text: *Hiss*
>The demon shrieks and becomes engulfed in flames as it disappears.
Alright, that's the last one!
Now to see if this place will go away too...!!
>The flames sear the demon as it vanishes.
This trembling... Does this mean the Aura Gate is about to disappear?
No, this feels wrong. What is...?
Watch out...! Something's coming!
>The trembling continues as fissures beaming with light form in the air.
Yo, what the hell is that...?
*Chuckle*

*Laugh*
I have been revived at last!
>The demon laughs wholeheartedly...
It's not even looking at us, but its presence...
This is probably bad, isn't it?
Ah... Something must have come over me after the seal was broken.
You, humans!
Well done.
I am Adramelech.
I am the sun god you have resurrected by felling those demons.
Yo, the ones we just...?
The other crazed solar deities...? You're here because...?
Feel no shame in not knowing due to ignorance.
I am the very one that hatched this scheme after all.
It went so well, I must applaud you and myself...
Your powers as demon users alone would have sufficed,
but having this labyrinth morph to egg you on was simply brilliant of me!
So you're the one behind this place then...
Indeed. I created this realm using the power of the Aura,
and in order to resurrect myself through the power of the sun.
But I may not have needed to bother with this,
and possibly harnessed this power directly to serve my goals.
This Aura is just a sliver of HIS power.
It was quite troublesome building this place up to this degree.
The Aura is a part of God...?
Anyways, my scheme succeeded and I am content with that.
Now. You also did very well for yourselves.
You have my gratitude.
Your reward shall be to nourish me as my next meal.
Yo, we ain't just gonna let that happen!
Get ready, y'all! Devil Download!
>The Liberators' demons attack all at once!
Fools... Can you not see that you are no match?
Hah!
>Adramelech sets everything ablaze by waving his peacock feathers.
*Screech*
*Groan*
*Scream*
A-All those at once?!
Ah, but there are some left. Let them burn...! Hah!
>The air begins to swelter when Adramelech streches out his hand.
*Roar*
*Groan*
>The demons collapse one by one as the air around them burns...!
Humans... I suppose this is all you can muster.
>The unbearable heat wave begins to spread...!
>It becomes too much!
No!!
Hm... You are still standing...
You humans may be tougher than I initially thought...
>Adramelech stands idle but lets his evil energy swell...!
Shit... He's strong...

*Chuckle*
Well, of course.
Do not be such a bother. I may just forget to control myself.
If that happens, my meal will end up vanishing as a result.
Ugh...
No...
Now... To deal with those blasted angels. Then to remake this world.
I must prepare for HIS return from hiding,
and have a world befitting of him ready when he arrives.
There is much work to be done.
It seems I will not be able to savor this meal. But who to start with...?
(Shit... At this rate, we're all done for...!)
Wh-What is the meaning of this? You are the sun god?
And I am supposed to be your envoy?
Such evil... Such hideousness...
Me... Hideous?
Not only are you powerless, you are blind as well?
What was my purpose in life about then...?
Your purpose? But of course, your purpose as a pathetic human has been set in stone.
You are to become the very source of my growing powers!
No... This can't be...
>Yoji staggers forward like a newborn fawn.
Yoji, no!! What are you doing?!
Ah, your tongue is filthy, and yet you come hither. Very admirable.
Then you shall be the first... Come and nourish me!
Megakin!!
>Megakin desperately chases after Yoji and tries to reach out to him!
?! What?! How?!
*Roar*
>Adramelech falls to his knees...!
>Adramelech sees Yoji standing over him, glowing with light.
W-What just happened...?!
No idea. I didn't think Megakin made it to him in time but...
Yoji... What the?
What is the meaning of this...?!
How is a lowly human in possession of Uriel's powers?!
